Code of Conduct
As contributors and maintainers of this repository, we are committed to fostering an inclusive and welcoming environment for all participants. We value the involvement of individuals from diverse backgrounds and perspectives and strive to create a respectful and collaborative space. To ensure a positive experience for everyone, we have established the following Code of Conduct, which applies to all interactions within this repository and its associated community:

1. Be Respectful
Treat others with respect and kindness. Be considerate of differing opinions and experiences. Disagreements and constructive discussions are welcome, but personal attacks, harassment, or discrimination of any form will not be tolerated.

2. Foster Inclusivity
Embrace diversity and inclusivity. Create an environment where everyone feels welcome, regardless of their race, ethnicity, gender identity, sexual orientation, disability, age, or any other personal attribute. Be mindful of language and actions that may exclude or marginalize others.

3. Encourage Collaboration
Promote a collaborative atmosphere by supporting and uplifting fellow contributors. Share knowledge, ideas, and feedback constructively. Be open to learning from others and consider alternative perspectives. Help create a community where everyone can grow and improve together.

4. Be Professional
Maintain a professional demeanor in all interactions. Refrain from engaging in disruptive or abusive behavior. Respect the boundaries and privacy of others. Remember that this repository is primarily focused on learning and teaching, and professionalism is crucial to fostering a positive educational environment.

5. Respect Intellectual Property
Honor copyright laws and intellectual property rights. Do not plagiarize or violate the licenses of code, documentation, or any other materials shared within this repository. Give proper attribution when using or referring to the work of others.

6. Reporting Violations
If you witness or experience any violations of this Code of Conduct, please report them to the repository maintainers by contacting us by email. All reports will be handled with discretion and will be promptly reviewed and addressed.

7. Consequences
Unacceptable behavior, as determined by the repository maintainers, may result in temporary or permanent restrictions from participating in this repository and its associated community activities. The severity of the consequences will depend on the nature and extent of the violation.

By participating in this repository, you agree to abide by this Code of Conduct. We are committed to enforcing this Code of Conduct and maintaining a safe and inclusive environment for all contributors.
